President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Henry Kerner to the Office of Special Counsel. If confirmed, Kerner, who hails from California, will serve as the Special Counsel in the Office of Special Counsel. Kerner has a law degree from Harvard Law School and has worked as a career prosecutor in California for nearly 20 years. He has also worked on the staff of the House Oversight Committee and led investigations of the Federal bureaucracy under Chairman Darrell Issa and Chairman Chaffetz. Kerner has also served as the Staff Director under Ranking Member Sen. John McCain of the Senate Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations. He later became a Vice President at Cause of Action, a nonpartisan oversight group dedicated to exposing waste, fraud, and abuse in the Federal Government.